    "summary": "Merge multiple boolean checks on the same integer value when each check denotes a contiguous ConstantRange. In particular, a masked equality of the form `icmp eq/ne (and X, M), C` with `M = -2^k` and `C` aligned to `2^k` denotes the contiguous range `[C, C + 2^k)` modulo bitwidth. If another compare on the same underlying value X (possibly after add/sub normalization) also denotes a ConstantRange, then InstCombine can intersect ranges for logical AND or union them for logical OR, replacing the pair of checks with a single simpler compare/range check when representable.",
